00:04:11.480 --> 00:04:13.760
And there was a name
given to the third Dalai

00:04:13.760 --> 00:04:17.600
Lama by a Mongolian emperor.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:20.660
Although, the Mongolians
had never seen the ocean,

00:04:20.660 --> 00:04:22.180
that particular one.

00:04:22.180 --> 00:04:25.900
But the steppe, the great steppe
is like an ocean of grass.

00:04:25.900 --> 00:04:27.620
So Dalai means huge.

00:04:27.620 --> 00:04:30.520
And the idea is the ocean
of wisdom and compassion.

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:32.260
That's the idea of Dalai Lama.

00:04:32.260 --> 00:04:34.630
Lama just means guru in Tibetan.

00:04:34.630 --> 00:04:38.930
But in a way, Tibetan
translation of guru into Lama

00:04:38.930 --> 00:04:42.170
shows how Tibetans
refined the Buddhist

00:04:42.170 --> 00:04:44.690
side of ancient Indian
culture, in a sense.

00:04:44.690 --> 00:04:46.940
It's very instructive
in the sense

00:04:46.940 --> 00:04:50.610
that guru comes from the
Indian word, Sanskrit word,

00:04:50.610 --> 00:04:54.140
for heavy, which reflects
the patriarchal nature

00:04:54.140 --> 00:04:57.430
of Indian society, the
heavy on top of your head

00:04:57.430 --> 00:05:00.860
like weighing you down.

00:05:00.860 --> 00:05:04.730
Whereas Lama means someone
you can't get past.

00:05:04.730 --> 00:05:06.950
It means you can't get beyond.

00:05:06.950 --> 00:05:10.520
So I always like to say instead
of some sort of heavy weight

00:05:10.520 --> 00:05:13.670
on top of your head, he's like
a real-- a good guru is really

00:05:13.670 --> 00:05:14.975
like Tar Baby.

00:05:14.975 --> 00:05:16.780
You know in the old--
what comic was that?

00:05:16.780 --> 00:05:17.900
Was that "Pogo" or something?

00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:18.710
It was some ancient thing.

00:05:18.710 --> 00:05:19.750
AUDIENCE: Brer Rabbit.

00:05:19.750 --> 00:05:21.375
ROBERT THURMAN: Brer
Rabbit, that's it.

00:05:21.375 --> 00:05:23.021
And Tar Baby is
like-- you try to--

00:05:23.021 --> 00:05:23.770
Tar Baby is there.

00:05:23.770 --> 00:05:24.830
And you want to get rid of him.

00:05:24.830 --> 00:05:26.645
You don't want guru bugging
you and following you

00:05:26.645 --> 00:05:28.270
around the whole time
and making you do

00:05:28.270 --> 00:05:29.870
whatever you're supposed to do.

00:05:29.870 --> 00:05:31.435
And so, you want
to get rid of him.

00:05:31.435 --> 00:05:32.810
But then Tar Baby
was-- you would

00:05:32.810 --> 00:05:35.592
grab Tar Baby to get rid of him
and then you'd be stuck to him.

00:05:35.592 --> 00:05:37.550
You couldn't like-- you
couldn't eliminate him.

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:39.470
So you couldn't get past him.

00:05:39.470 --> 00:05:41.690
So the key point in
the Tibetan thing

00:05:41.690 --> 00:05:44.270
is they realized that
the teacher is not just

00:05:44.270 --> 00:05:46.310
a weight on top of your head.

00:05:46.310 --> 00:05:49.130
And the whole thing is not
just to revere the teacher--

00:05:49.130 --> 00:05:50.540
although, they do.

00:05:50.540 --> 00:05:53.630
But it is to
execute the teaching

00:05:53.630 --> 00:05:57.160
that the teacher gives you
and become a teacher yourself.

00:05:57.160 --> 00:05:59.630
So that's what the guru
wants you to do that.

00:05:59.630 --> 00:06:02.750
And in Buddhism in
Indian civilization,

00:06:02.750 --> 00:06:08.840
the guru role was somewhat
undermined by the exoteric idea

00:06:08.840 --> 00:06:11.990
of the teacher as
[INAUDIBLE] what they call,

00:06:11.990 --> 00:06:14.710
which means a virtuous friend.

00:06:14.710 --> 00:06:17.240
So the idea of a teacher is
like a friend who inspires you

00:06:17.240 --> 00:06:20.270
rather than an authority who
sits on top of you, which

00:06:20.270 --> 00:06:22.770
might have been the norm
in ordinary Indian culture

00:06:22.770 --> 00:06:24.230
before Buddha's time.

00:06:24.230 --> 00:06:26.900
He was a bit of a
rebel, the Buddha.

00:06:26.900 --> 00:06:29.330
He didn't do what
his dad told him.

00:06:29.330 --> 00:06:30.320
He should be a King.

00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:33.150
He went off to become
enlightened, whatever that is.

00:06:33.150 --> 00:06:37.970
And his dad did what dads do
when young men, or women, don't

00:06:37.970 --> 00:06:39.200
do what they say.

00:06:39.200 --> 00:06:41.120
Locked him up.

00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:43.430
And sent in some Brahman
priest psychiatrists

00:06:43.430 --> 00:06:46.220
to try to get him to
shape up to be a King.

00:06:46.220 --> 00:06:50.240
And so, what he did-- what
rugged individuals do--

00:06:50.240 --> 00:06:52.070
he escaped.

00:06:52.070 --> 00:06:53.910
And ran off into the jungle.

00:06:53.910 --> 00:06:59.270
Anyway, so Dalai Lama,
that's Dalai Lama means.

00:06:59.270 --> 00:07:02.500
