Thank you.

00:48:59.730 --> 00:49:01.980
SPEAKER 3: So one of the
terms used for the Dalai Lama

00:49:01.980 --> 00:49:03.391
is kundun, or the presence--

00:49:03.391 --> 00:49:05.140
ROBERT THURMAN: Kundun
means the presence.

00:49:05.140 --> 00:49:07.050
Right, that's an honorific term.

00:49:07.050 --> 00:49:08.280
SPEAKER 3: I've always
found that mysterious.

00:49:08.280 --> 00:49:10.238
I was wondering if you
could unpack that a bit.

00:49:10.238 --> 00:49:12.866
ROBERT THURMAN: Well,
that's the nature of--

00:49:12.866 --> 00:49:14.490
well, this relates
to an enlightenment.

00:49:14.490 --> 00:49:16.380
What is enlightenment?

00:49:16.380 --> 00:49:18.351
Westerners wrongly think
that enlightenment--

00:49:18.351 --> 00:49:19.350
but I stick to the term.

00:49:19.350 --> 00:49:22.380
I don't so much like awakening,
but it's not wrong either.

00:49:22.380 --> 00:49:24.006
But I like enlightenment.

00:49:24.006 --> 00:49:25.380
But the thing
enlightenment means

00:49:25.380 --> 00:49:29.400
that some probably usually
male guy big light bulb

00:49:29.400 --> 00:49:30.760
goes off in his head.

00:49:30.760 --> 00:49:33.760
And then he walks around
acting holy and lights flow out

00:49:33.760 --> 00:49:34.260
of his head.

00:49:34.260 --> 00:49:36.780
And everybody goes, oh,
[INAUDIBLE],, yes, you

00:49:36.780 --> 00:49:37.720
need a Cadillac.

00:49:37.720 --> 00:49:40.270
I got one for you,
a Rolls Royce even.

00:49:40.270 --> 00:49:43.060
That's ridiculous
business, authority thing.

00:49:43.060 --> 00:49:44.650
Enlightenment
actually is defined

00:49:44.650 --> 00:49:49.980
as someone who realizes
selflessness as a reality

00:49:49.980 --> 00:49:52.080
check, out of a reality check.

00:49:52.080 --> 00:49:54.520
In other words, it doesn't
mean they don't exist.

00:49:54.520 --> 00:49:57.060
Selflessness means that you
are relational-- your self is

00:49:57.060 --> 00:50:00.180
a relational construct,
which you are constantly

00:50:00.180 --> 00:50:02.290
either improving or
it's deteriorating

00:50:02.290 --> 00:50:06.190
if you watch too many
commercials and too much CNN.

00:50:06.190 --> 00:50:09.480
CNN creates your fear
and anger and despair.

00:50:09.480 --> 00:50:12.126
And the commercials create
your greed and dissatisfaction.

00:50:12.126 --> 00:50:13.500
So if you watch
too much of that,

00:50:13.500 --> 00:50:15.270
your self deteriorates
and becomes

00:50:15.270 --> 00:50:17.460
more frustrated and discontent.

00:50:17.460 --> 00:50:21.640
If you watch the Dalai Lama,
if you study, if you meditate,

00:50:21.640 --> 00:50:23.370
if you think about
peace and love,

00:50:23.370 --> 00:50:26.310
and Google do no evil
looking through the two O's

00:50:26.310 --> 00:50:30.220
of the Google, then you get
better and better all the time.

00:50:30.220 --> 00:50:35.190
So selflessness means there's no
fixed, rigid identity in there.

00:50:35.190 --> 00:50:37.090
And when you realize
that, then you

00:50:37.090 --> 00:50:39.810
become interactively
more selfless,

00:50:39.810 --> 00:50:41.430
meaning loving
and compassionate.

00:50:41.430 --> 00:50:43.860
That's how enlightenment
is defined.

00:50:43.860 --> 00:50:45.540
So you might not be
glowing with light

00:50:45.540 --> 00:50:47.956
because you might be out there
healing someone, or helping

00:50:47.956 --> 00:50:51.830
them, or making something
that helps them,

00:50:51.830 --> 00:50:53.400
or even doing
business and really

00:50:53.400 --> 00:50:55.230
making your customer
happy as business

00:50:55.230 --> 00:50:57.769
is supposed to be doing,
not just grabbing stuff

00:50:57.769 --> 00:50:58.560
from your customer.

00:50:58.560 --> 00:51:00.675
But making them happy
by doing them a service.

00:51:04.500 --> 00:51:07.470
So the presence, therefore,
comes from the fact

00:51:07.470 --> 00:51:11.040
that the Dalai Lama is
perceived by people who meet him

00:51:11.040 --> 00:51:13.770
as having a presence
where when you meet

00:51:13.770 --> 00:51:17.400
you feel enfolded in a
friendly, loving presence,

00:51:17.400 --> 00:51:22.010
like a child feels when
they meet their mom.

00:51:22.010 --> 00:51:25.820
Or a beloved feels when
they meet their beloved, who

00:51:25.820 --> 00:51:28.170
hopefully loves them.

00:51:28.170 --> 00:51:31.590
Sometimes that
happens for a while.

00:51:31.590 --> 00:51:35.130
Although, don't get me
wrong, 50th anniversary we

00:51:35.130 --> 00:51:37.170
had this summer, me and my wife.

00:51:37.170 --> 00:51:39.210
So we've hung in there.

00:51:39.210 --> 00:51:40.800
And she's a saint.

00:51:40.800 --> 00:51:43.310
I'm just lucky.

00:51:43.310 --> 00:51:45.570
And so point is the
presence means this is

00:51:45.570 --> 00:51:47.340
a presence where you become--

00:51:47.340 --> 00:51:51.600
you feel like you're in
a positive field, a field

00:51:51.600 --> 00:51:55.440
of calm, a field of finding
your own inner well-being,

00:51:55.440 --> 00:51:57.720
which is your inner
happiness-- not just pleasure,

00:51:57.720 --> 00:51:59.160
but inner happiness.

00:51:59.160 --> 00:52:01.920
And you feel that the
world is not against you.

00:52:01.920 --> 00:52:04.500
And you feel someone
who is for you and who

00:52:04.500 --> 00:52:06.180
is interested in you.

00:52:06.180 --> 00:52:09.900
My wife once-- one guy once
asked me at a luncheon--

00:52:09.900 --> 00:52:12.619
wealthy guy who was
a guru collector--

00:52:12.619 --> 00:52:14.660
he said, you've known the
Dalai Lama a long time.

00:52:14.660 --> 00:52:16.940
Have you ever seen
him do a miracle?

00:52:16.940 --> 00:52:18.180
He got all excited.

00:52:18.180 --> 00:52:20.249
And I didn't know
what to say because I

00:52:20.249 --> 00:52:22.540
have seen a few unusual
things, but you're not supposed

00:52:22.540 --> 00:52:23.540
to really talk about it.

00:52:23.540 --> 00:52:25.010
So I'm hemming and hawing.

00:52:25.010 --> 00:52:28.202
And my wife says,
oh yeah, many times.

00:52:28.202 --> 00:52:29.110
And I go, what?

00:52:29.110 --> 00:52:30.625
What is she going to say?

00:52:30.625 --> 00:52:32.783
I'm like, oh no.

00:52:32.783 --> 00:52:34.850
And so then, he's leaning
forward in his chair.

00:52:34.850 --> 00:52:38.355
And she says, I've seen him
in many occasions, very busy,

00:52:38.355 --> 00:52:41.190
a lot of people around,
everybody wants a piece of him.

00:52:41.190 --> 00:52:44.730
He's on a tour, or a
teaching, or whatever,

00:52:44.730 --> 00:52:47.610
and I have never seen him
ever in any of those times

00:52:47.610 --> 00:52:51.000
fail to give his total
concentration and attention

00:52:51.000 --> 00:52:53.970
to whomever he was sitting with.

00:52:53.970 --> 00:52:56.280
And that's a miracle, she says.

00:52:56.280 --> 00:52:57.280
And the guy goes, oh.

00:53:00.870 --> 00:53:02.340
He didn't understand.

00:53:02.340 --> 00:53:05.250
I was really pleased
and I was educated

00:53:05.250 --> 00:53:08.850
by my final girl, who is she.

00:53:08.850 --> 00:53:11.460
And that's what-- that's why
the call the presence because

00:53:11.460 --> 00:53:14.099
in their presence
you feel cheered up.

00:53:14.099 --> 00:53:15.390
And so what we've tried to do--

00:53:15.390 --> 00:53:16.660
thank you for that question.

00:53:16.660 --> 00:53:19.260
So this book is the
presence of the Dalai Lama.

00:53:19.260 --> 00:53:22.110
And it makes it more real
that we show the difficulties

00:53:22.110 --> 00:53:26.160
that he's had not just with the
Chinese, but people like Nixon,

00:53:26.160 --> 00:53:27.110
with the Brits--

00:53:27.110 --> 00:53:28.140
the Brexit people.

00:53:28.140 --> 00:53:30.140
We're going to simply
secede from the world.

00:53:30.140 --> 00:53:31.280
Give me a break.

00:53:35.370 --> 00:53:39.030
Yet he has maintains himself
as our presence-- the presence.

00:53:39.030 --> 00:53:41.237
And everybody feels
it, but they don't--

00:53:41.237 --> 00:53:42.570
even they don't know what it is.

00:53:42.570 --> 00:53:44.310
But here then, they'll
know what it is.

00:53:44.310 --> 00:53:46.410
And they will also
realize, which

00:53:46.410 --> 00:53:49.020
is really key for
our country now,

00:53:49.020 --> 00:53:51.690
that despair is not an option.

00:53:51.690 --> 00:53:56.070
And non-engagement, and not
voting, and not participating,

00:53:56.070 --> 00:53:59.160
and not keeping informed,
and not calling them out

00:53:59.160 --> 00:53:59.910
is not an option.

00:53:59.910 --> 00:54:02.300
Also, not doing violence
is not an option either.

00:54:02.300 --> 00:54:04.170
But being really
actively engaged

00:54:04.170 --> 00:54:07.260
in making this wonderful
gift of democracy

00:54:07.260 --> 00:54:10.510
that we have been given, that
has now crumbled and is really

00:54:10.510 --> 00:54:11.760
finished actually temporarily.

00:54:11.760 --> 00:54:13.407
It's now money-ocracy.

00:54:13.407 --> 00:54:14.240
There's no question.

00:54:14.240 --> 00:54:15.720
It's plutocracy.

00:54:15.720 --> 00:54:17.700
It's oligarchy.

00:54:17.700 --> 00:54:18.810
We can still do it.

00:54:18.810 --> 00:54:20.620
We have a system where
we can still do it.

00:54:20.620 --> 00:54:25.320
If 80% or 85% engage
fully, as Michael Moore--

00:54:25.320 --> 00:54:26.879
Michael Moore is
going to run for--

00:54:26.879 --> 00:54:27.420
I don't know.

00:54:27.420 --> 00:54:29.310
Fashion consultant, I think.

00:54:29.310 --> 00:54:30.270
I'm not sure.

00:54:30.270 --> 00:54:33.210
Dogcatcher or president
or senator, but everybody

00:54:33.210 --> 00:54:36.420
has to run for everything
in a friendly, joyful way,

00:54:36.420 --> 00:54:39.750
happily, not angrily
and not upset.

00:54:39.750 --> 00:54:41.734
And that's the
message we all need.

00:54:41.734 --> 00:54:42.900
And this book will help you.

00:54:42.900 --> 00:54:44.110
So get the book.

00:54:44.110 --> 00:54:44.830
You'll enjoy it.

00:54:44.830 --> 00:54:47.160
Thank you very much.

